## Audit Trail

### Status History Schema

```
{
  entityType: "<YourEntity>",
  entityId: "entity-123",
  fromStatus: "pending",
  toStatus: "active",
  actor: {
    userId: "user-456",
    role: "admin",
    name: "Actor Name"
  },
  reason: "Approved after review",  // optional
  metadata: { ... },                // optional context
  timestamp: "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
}
```

### Rules

- **Append-only** - avoid editing or deleting status history records. Exception: GDPR erasure requests and PII redaction may require removal/anonymization.
- **Every transition creates a history record** - high-frequency state churn (real-time counters, ranking changes) may batch/aggregate history instead of per-event logging.
- **Include actor identity** - who triggered this change (user, system, cron job)
- **Include reason** for manual transitions (admin adding a note)
- **Queryable** - "show me all status changes for entity X" is a common need
- **Displayable** - consider exposing a timeline/activity log of status changes if useful to users

