## UI Patterns for Status

### Status Badge

```
Every status has:
  - Label: human-readable text ("Draft", "In Review", "Active")
  - Color: semantic color from design system
  - Icon: optional icon (clock for pending, check for completed)

Color mapping (semantic):
  Draft / Pending    -> gray or blue (neutral, waiting)
  Active / In Progress -> blue or purple (ongoing)
  Approved / Success -> green (positive outcome)
  Completed / Done   -> green (final positive)
  Needs Attention    -> amber/orange (action required)
  Cancelled / Failed -> red (negative outcome)
  Resolved / Closed  -> gray (no further action)
```

### Status Timeline

```
Show the full journey of an entity:

  [x] Draft                  Jan 10, 10:00 AM    Created by John
  [x] In Review              Jan 10, 10:05 AM    Submitted for review
  [x] Approved               Jan 10, 10:07 AM    Reviewer signed off
  [x] Active                 Jan 11, 09:00 AM    Published by admin
  [ ] Archived               (expected Jan 12)
  [ ] Closed

  [x] = completed step    [ ] = upcoming step
```

### Available Actions Based on State

```
Only show buttons/actions that are valid for the current state:

  Status: Draft
    [Submit for Review]  [Discard Draft]     <- shown

  Status: In Review
    [Approve]  [Reject]                     <- shown
    [Discard Draft]                          <- hidden (can't discard after submission)

  Status: Active
    [Archive]                                <- shown
    (no other actions)                       <- nothing else applicable
```

**Rule**: Prefer hiding or disabling buttons for invalid transitions. In distributed systems, race conditions may still cause errors after render - handle gracefully with a retry or refresh.

